HOUSE RESOLUTION 211
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Ariel Paige Hutson, 2026
Valedictorian at Scott County High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Ariel Paige Hutson is one such exceptional student, who was recently
named Valedictorian of the 2026 graduating class at Scott County High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Hutson has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Ariel Hutson has earned an
exemplary grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, her display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for her
future success; and
WHEREAS, Ariel Hutson's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for
her family, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Hutson's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of this legislative body; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby
commend and honor Ariel Paige Hutson of Scott County High School on being named the 2026
